    • Constructor Detail

      • EmpBoundingBox

        public EmpBoundingBox()
        This is the default constructor.

      • EmpBoundingBox

        public EmpBoundingBox(double northValue,
                      double southValue,
                      double eastValue,
                      double westValue)
        This constructor defines an area bounded by the north, south, east, and west parameters provided.
        Parameters:
        northValue - The most northern latitude of the area. If this value is less than southValue, the values are swapped.
        southValue - The most southern latitude of the area. If this value is greater than northValue, the values are swapped.
        eastValue - The east longitude of the area. If the east value is greater than the west value the area contains the international date line.
        westValue - The west longitude of the area. If the west value is less than the east value the area contains the international date line.

      • EmpBoundingBox

        public EmpBoundingBox(IGeoPosition southWest,
                      IGeoPosition northEast)
        This constructor defines an area bounded by the northEast and southWest coordinates.
        Parameters:
        southWest - The coordinates of the south west point of the bounding area.
        northEast - The coordinates of the north east point of the bounding area.
